  "headline": "Learning How to Learn",
  "description": "Learning how to learn is a meta-skill that improves all other skills. Key techniques: spaced repetition (review at increasing intervals), active recall (test yourself, don't re-read), interleaving (mix topics, don't block), elaboration (explain in your own words), and focused + diffuse thinking modes (Pomodoro + rest).",
